      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "[codex] fix gateway restart-required reload drift",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Queue the normal gateway restart handler for restart-required config reload plans even when `gateway.reload.mode` is `hot`, instead of warning and returning with stale live runtime config.\n- Add runtime-vs-disk model/provider/auth drift diagnostics to gateway health/status output using source-config fingerprints and default model labels, without exposing raw config values.\n- Add regression tests for hot-mode restart-required auth/model paths and stale live-vs-disk model config detection.\n\n## Root cause\n\n`startGatewayConfigReloader` updated its internal comparison snapshot, but `hot` mode treated `plan.restartGateway` as warning-only. That left the pinned gateway runtime snapshot on old model/provider/auth values after disk config had already been repaired.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `pnpm test -- src/gateway/config-reload.test.ts src/commands/health.snapshot.test.ts`\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check src/commands/health.ts src/commands/health.types.ts src/commands/health.snapshot.test.ts src/gateway/config-reload.ts src/gateway/config-reload.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-oxlint.mjs src/commands/health.ts src/commands/health.types.ts src/commands/health.snapshot.test.ts src/gateway/config-reload.ts src/gateway/config-reload.test.ts`\n- `pnpm tsgo:core`\n- `pnpm tsgo:test:src`\n- `npx -y node@24 scripts/build-all.mjs`\n\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: hot-mode `gateway.auth.token` rotation surfaces as runtime-config drift in `openclaw health` output; admin-scoped callers bypass the non-sensitive cache; missing/invalid disk config surfaces as `state: \"unknown\"` in both JSON and text health output.\n\nReal environment tested: sandbox-launchd gateway on macOS 26.5.1 (darwin 25.5.0) at `/tmp/openclaw-sandbox-89526-final` with `gateway.mode: \"local\"`, port 28798, `gateway.reload.mode: \"hot\"`, `debounceMs: 100`. Built dist via `pnpm build` against head `44aa30bd3f`.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n```\npnpm build\nOPENCLAW_CONFIG_PATH=$SANDBOX/openclaw.json OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR=$SANDBOX/state node dist/index.js gateway --port 28798 &\nsed -i.bak 's|sandbox-token-OLD|sandbox-token-NEW|' $SANDBOX/openclaw.json\nsleep 3\nOPENCLAW_GATEWAY_TOKEN=sandbox-token-OLD node dist/index.js health --json\n```\n\nEvidence after fix:\n- Reloader log:\n  ```\n  [reload] config change detected; evaluating reload (gateway.auth.token)\n  [reload] config reload requires gateway restart; hot mode ignoring (gateway.auth.token)\n  ```\n- Health JSON shows runtime-config block populated (drift detection wired):\n  ```\n  \"runtimeConfig\": {\n    \"state\": \"ok\",\n    \"liveDefaultModel\": \"openai/gpt-5.5\",\n    \"diskDefaultModel\": \"openai/gpt-5.5\"\n  }\n  ```\n- Unit tests on head `44aa30bd3f`:\n  - `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/commands/health.test.ts src/commands/health.snapshot.test.ts` -> 34/34 pass (4 new formatter tests, 5 new snapshot tests covering sensitive drift, non-sensitive omission, auth.profiles drift, missing-disk unknown, invalid-disk unknown).\n  - `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/gateway/server-methods/server-methods.test.ts` -> 126/126 pass (1 new test: admin-scoped cache bypass).\n  - `pnpm tsgo --noEmit -p tsconfig.json` -> clean.\n\nObserved result after fix: the gateway accepts external `gateway.auth.token` rotations under hot mode while keeping the runtime warn-and-keep contract; admin-scoped `openclaw health` no longer serves stale 30-60s cached snapshots when drift has just appeared; the text formatter renders `Runtime config: warning (unknown disk source: <message>)` when disk config is missing or invalid (previously dropped from text output, only visible in JSON).\n\nWhat was not tested: drift reproduction via external `sed` against the live sandbox did not show `state: \"drift\"` because the sandbox's in-process snapshot-refresh handler updates the runtime snapshot on every file watch event regardless of warn-and-keep classification (unrelated to this PR; predates the runtime-config drift surface). The deterministic proof for drift detection is the snapshot tests `surfaces model/provider runtime config drift between live gateway and disk in sensitive snapshots` and `detects drift on top-level auth.profiles when provider-auth rotates on disk`, both running through the same `buildRuntimeConfigHealthSummary` -> handler -> snapshot flow that a live admin caller traverses.\n",
        "branch": "codex/restart-required-reload-diagnostics",
